text: Iowa State University of Science and Technology or as it is better known, Iowa State University is a public university in Ames, Iowa. The university has about 33,000 students. It was founded in 1858. The president of the university is Wendy Wintersteen. George Washington Carver was a student at Iowa State. ==Sports== The athletics teams of the university are called the Cyclones. They have 16 varsity teams and they compete in the Big 12 Conference. ==Other websites== *Iowa State University's Official website Category:Association of American Universities Category:Big 12 Conference Category:Colleges and universities in Iowa Category:1858 establishments in the United States Category:1850s establishments in Iowa
